Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has confirmed 20 new cases of coronavirus. “Twenty new cases of #COVID19 have been reported in Nigeria; 13 in Lagos, 4 in FCT, 2 in Kaduna and 1 in Oyo State,” the NCDC said on Twitter on Monday. “As at 09:00 pm 30th March there are 131 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria with 2 deaths.”  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .